<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12093n"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12093n">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12093n"> 93(n)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> nuptial feast, seated on ladders</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Pour les grandes noces, quand les invit&eacute;s sont au nombre de plusieurs centaines, &agrave; la belle saison, le repas a lieu en plein air; des &eacute;chelles pos&eacute;es sur leur longueur perpendiculairement au sol et solidement fix&eacute;es, forment des bancs immenses et ing&eacute;nieux. Le couvert est alors dress&eacute; par terre, entre deux rang&eacute;es d&apos;&eacute;chelles. <br><font color="green">[For great wedding parties, when there are several hundred guests and in the summer, the meal is set outdoors; ladders laid lengthwise perpendicularly to the ground and solidly attached, become immense and ingenious seating arrangements. The meal is served on the ground between two rows of ladders.]</font> <small> Paul-Yves S&eacute;billot, <a name="PYLB" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#PYLB"><cite title="source">La Bretagne et ses Traditions</cite></a> (1898) 121</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
